We're advertising two jobs, across mathematics:

http://www.jobs.ac.uk/job/AEY602/lecturer-senior-lecturer-reader/

To give the usual explanation about the British system: these are all
open-ended positions (i.e. the closest the UK comes to tenure).  The four
levels for academics here are, in order, Lecturer, Senior Lecturer, Reader
and Professor; we're advertising at all levels except the last.

I'm about to move to the University of Edinburgh, but plenty of people
with categorical interests will remain at Glasgow (e.g. Richard Steiner,
Danny Stevenson, Uli Kraehmer, Andy Baker).  There's also Neil Ghani and
co. a short hop away at Strathclyde.

Best wishes,
Tom



